etymology.description: 又(又) (yòu, "again") + 肉(肉) (ròu, "meat") = hand with meat -> intricate structure
etymology.interpretation: 㞢 is an ancient form of 有(有) (yǒu, "have"), suggesting possession or holding. The combination of 又(又) (yòu, "again") as a phonetic component and 肉(肉) (ròu, "meat") as a semantic element metaphorically represents holding or having an intricate structure.
